 sense to do inside the<br />loop-over-apics in enable_IO_APIC, no?<br /><br />Especially since that one already calculates the number of entries, and<br />does it a lot more nicely than you do.. (ie no shifting and masking with<br />magic constants).<br /><br />Finally, the third issue I have is that _if_ the MP table is correct,<br />we'll never know. Wouldn't it be better to query the MP table regardless,<br />and see if it agrees with what we found, and if it doesn't, at least print<br />a message so that it is easier to debug things if sh*t happens?<br /><br />		Linus<br />-<br />To unsubscribe from this list: send the line "unsubscribe linux-kernel" in<br />the body of a message to majordomo&#64;vger.kernel.org<br />More majordomo info at  <a href="http://vger.kernel.org/majordomo-info.html">http://vger.kernel.org/majordomo-info.html</a><br />Please read the FAQ at  <a href="http://www.tux.org/lkml/">http://www.tux.org/lkml/</a><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
